  m_Name: Ribcage_and_Sternum.001
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Ribcage_and_Sternum.001
  partName: Ribcage and Sternum 001
  descriptionChunks:
  - The ribcage and sternum form the protective thoracic framework surrounding the
    canine heart, lungs, and major blood vessels. The ribs articulate with the thoracic
    vertebrae and connect ventrally to the sternum through costal cartilage, creating
    a flexible yet supportive cage.
  - This structure protects vital organs while allowing expansion and contraction
    during breathing. Muscles attached to the ribs and sternum contribute to respiration,
    posture, and forelimb movement. The thoracic cage also assists with shock absorption
    during locomotion.
